  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photographic plate</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1929</date>
      <persName role="Press Photographer Vreme"><forename>Svetozar </forename><surname>Grdijan</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.d2666bab">Grdijan, Svetozar </ref><certainty target="persName" cert="medium" locus="value" /></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Men and women in winter coats are sitting in the sun on benches in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=K3">Kalemegdan</ref>. The picture is taken from a distance – the people are paying no attention to the photographer. On the nearest bench, a woman and a man are sitting on opposite ends, as though they do not know each other. On a second bench, two ladies in fur coats are occupied with two toddlers and their pushchairs.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The photograph appeared in the newspaper Vreme in its 'Belgrade Chronicle' section. The accompanying title informed readers that Belgrade citizens were enjoying the first rays of sun in early spring.</ab>
